1
00:01:29,490 --> 00:01:34,920
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,460 --> 00:01:37,710
[Episode 23]

3
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:51,280
Xiaoman!

4
00:02:53,770 --> 00:02:54,560
Xiaoman!

5
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,750
When did you get back?

6
00:03:05,870 --> 00:03:07,330
Why didn't you let me know?

7
00:03:18,170 --> 00:03:18,730
Da.

8
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:24,990
I... I just...

9
00:03:28,079 --> 00:03:28,710
Da.

10
00:03:29,870 --> 00:03:30,800
Nana! Nana, quick!

11
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:31,910
Come here. Look.

12
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:35,440
Xiaoman?

13
00:03:35,470 --> 00:03:36,100
Nana.

14
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:37,079
You're back.

15
00:03:38,470 --> 00:03:39,930
Come to my place for a meal?

16
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,579
Let's have a drink.

17
00:03:42,650 --> 00:03:43,780
Well, about that...

18
00:03:44,630 --> 00:03:45,120
Forget it.

19
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:47,870
I just got back today.

20
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,560
I'll take a rain check.

21
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,910
Then tomorrow. Let's drink tomorrow.

22
00:03:50,910 --> 00:03:51,280
Right.

23
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:51,870
Okay?

24
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:53,520
Sure.

25
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:55,380
I'll come find you at your place tomorrow.

26
00:03:55,380 --> 00:03:56,400
Sure, anytime.

27
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,910
I'm off tomorrow.

28
00:03:57,910 --> 00:03:59,310
So come find me whenever.

29
00:04:03,950 --> 00:04:06,080
You get some rest. We're heading back.

30
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,800
We're leaving, Xiaoman.

31
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:10,960
Da.

32
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:12,560
Wait a second.

33
00:04:14,940 --> 00:04:15,540
What is it?

34
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:17,750
Well...

35
00:04:19,930 --> 00:04:22,089
I brought you a gift from Japan.

36
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,030
Well, you...

37
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,490
You'll definitely like it.

38
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,750
A helmet.

39
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:41,630
Wear it when you ride.

40
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,240
This is so cool.

41
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,920
We definitely have to drink tomorrow.

42
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,560
Okay.

43
00:04:51,630 --> 00:04:53,030
Alright, I'm going back.

44
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,040
Bye, Xiaoman.

45
00:04:58,530 --> 00:04:59,159
Bye.

46
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,360
Get some rest.

47
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:11,700
Don't you think
Xiaoman is acting a bit strange?

48
00:05:13,830 --> 00:05:15,560
I wonder what he's been through

49
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:16,830
these past few years.

50
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,820
Put this inside for me.

51
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:21,950
Ask him later.

52
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,560
I'll ask him tomorrow.

53
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,220
I'll have a good talk with him.

54
00:05:27,430 --> 00:05:29,230
Just put it on the cart. Let's go.

55
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:30,800
Are you still going to sit here?

56
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,950
I've been pedaling all day. I'm exhausted.

57
00:05:31,950 --> 00:05:34,880
I stood at the dance hall all day,
and my legs are sore.

58
00:06:02,910 --> 00:06:03,960
Xiaoman?

59
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:08,680
Mrs. Ding.

60
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,040
You're back.

61
00:06:10,060 --> 00:06:12,540
When did you get back?

62
00:06:12,570 --> 00:06:13,650
Just now.

63
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:15,660
Good boy.

64
00:06:16,630 --> 00:06:18,160
You've lost so much weight.

65
00:06:18,270 --> 00:06:19,510
Why are you so tanned?

66
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,560
But you're sturdy.

67
00:06:24,870 --> 00:06:26,160
Let me carry that for you.
Where did you go?

68
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:26,720
I...

69
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,070
I went to pick wild vegetables.

70
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:31,040
Come in, come on.

71
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:31,890
Go upstairs.

72
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,390
My Xiaoman is back!

73
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,510
Your mentor isn't home.

74
00:06:38,510 --> 00:06:40,310
How do I contact him to come back?

75
00:06:41,790 --> 00:06:43,050
Not this door anymore.

76
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,500
Not this door anymore.

77
00:06:45,159 --> 00:06:46,360
We've changed doors.

78
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:48,190
Your mentor said

79
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,750
he wanted a new look.

80
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:50,390
Come.

81
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,610
Come in this way.

82
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,140
So you enter through here now.

83
00:06:54,140 --> 00:06:54,900
Look.

84
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,390
It's changed.

85
00:06:56,909 --> 00:06:58,510
Your mentor sleeps here now,

86
00:06:58,950 --> 00:07:00,080
and I sleep in there.

87
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,710
Your mentor has gone out
to set up his stall

88
00:07:01,710 --> 00:07:03,310
without bringing his phone.

89
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,720
Xiaoman.

90
00:07:18,150 --> 00:07:19,480
I'll make you some food.

91
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:20,570
You must be hungry.

92
00:07:20,830 --> 00:07:22,630
Do you want some of my dumplings?

93
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:23,480
Yes.

94
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:29,750
Well...

95
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:30,510
This...

96
00:07:31,190 --> 00:07:32,630
Did you glue this at home?

97
00:07:32,630 --> 00:07:34,720
Yeah, I did it.

98
00:07:34,950 --> 00:07:36,510
Those bullets from back in the day

99
00:07:36,510 --> 00:07:37,600
are rare now.

100
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,680
Hard to find.

101
00:07:38,870 --> 00:07:40,000
How's my handiwork?

102
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:40,920
Not bad, right?

103
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,750
It's much better than what I had as a kid.

104
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:44,150
I glue them when I'm free.

105
00:07:44,370 --> 00:07:45,620
Then I go sell them.

106
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:47,280
It's nothing serious...

107
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,040
Just for fun.

108
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:51,480
Don't worry. Life is good.

109
00:07:53,060 --> 00:07:54,060
Eat something.

110
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:56,270
When will Mr. Ding be back?

111
00:07:56,390 --> 00:07:57,360
Your mentor...

112
00:07:57,870 --> 00:07:59,120
he only comes back

113
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,360
once a week now.

114
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:02,310
Why has he gone for so long?

115
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:04,170
Everyone around here moved away.

116
00:08:04,310 --> 00:08:05,390
It's empty.

117
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:07,810
No one buys his grilled chicken ribs.

118
00:08:07,830 --> 00:08:09,600
He goes to Tiecheng.

119
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:11,360
Do you know Bainiao Square?

120
00:08:11,430 --> 00:08:12,270
That's so far away.

121
00:08:12,270 --> 00:08:14,390
Exactly. So he just stays there.

122
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:16,050
He only comes back once a week.

123
00:08:16,510 --> 00:08:18,240
I stay here and watch the house.

124
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:30,600
Xiaoman.

125
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:33,390
Do me a favor.

126
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:34,909
Knead the dough.

127
00:08:34,909 --> 00:08:35,630
I'm going out.

128
00:08:35,630 --> 00:08:36,559
I'll do it. Okay.

129
00:08:36,580 --> 00:08:37,580
I'll do it. Here.

130
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,280
What's wrong?

131
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:40,120
Wait for me. Wait for me.

132
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,090
Are your hands okay?

133
00:09:53,790 --> 00:09:54,490
Kid.

134
00:09:58,280 --> 00:09:59,310
I'm fine. Well,

135
00:09:59,630 --> 00:10:01,030
I knocked over the basin.

136
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,550
The basin is fine. The basin is fine.

137
00:10:02,550 --> 00:10:03,810
As long as you're okay.

138
00:10:03,870 --> 00:10:05,130
What's wrong with you?

139
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:06,840
Don't scare me.

140
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:07,360
No, no.

141
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:08,140
Are you okay?

142
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:09,080
It's okay. It's okay.

143
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:09,960
They're not scraped, right?

144
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:10,600
It's okay. It's okay.

145
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,750
They're not scraped.

146
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:12,970
It's good they're not scraped.

147
00:10:12,970 --> 00:10:14,500
As long as there are no cuts.

148
00:10:14,510 --> 00:10:15,770
The bowls are fine too.

149
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:17,670
Leave it to me.

150
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:18,670
Let me do it.

151
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:19,990
It's okay. It's okay.

152
00:10:19,990 --> 00:10:21,120
Everything is fine.

153
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,080
It's okay.

154
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,150
Coming!

155
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:33,200
Xia Lei's mom.

156
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,480
Coming, coming.

157
00:10:37,910 --> 00:10:39,510
What is it? Why the rush?

158
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,660
Listen, I have something to tell you.

159
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,000
Xiaoman is back.

160
00:10:44,110 --> 00:10:45,790
He didn't even say he came back.

161
00:10:45,790 --> 00:10:46,670
Let's go see him together.

162
00:10:46,670 --> 00:10:47,530
Let me tell you.

163
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:48,510
Well, put that aside.

164
00:10:48,510 --> 00:10:49,320
Listen to me.

165
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:51,790
Well, Xiaoman

166
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,530
seems to have a problem.

167
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:54,990
What happened to him?

168
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,460
I can't put my finger on it.

169
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,600
I thought since you work at the hospital,

170
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,860
you might understand.

171
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,250
I have to talk to you.

172
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,290
No rush. Come on.

173
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:21,830
Da.

174
00:11:23,430 --> 00:11:25,230
Why did you close the dance hall?

175
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,870
No one dances anymore.

176
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:29,580
I can't pay wages. Why keep it open?

177
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,390
A big boss like you

178
00:11:31,390 --> 00:11:33,720
is riding a tricycle.
Not doing business anymore?

179
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,840
I'll do business later.

180
00:11:36,870 --> 00:11:38,600
I need to fill my stomach first.

181
00:12:17,710 --> 00:12:19,310
They're still green grapes.

182
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:22,440
Don't set your teeth on edge.

183
00:12:33,030 --> 00:12:35,030
You little brat, why are you running?

184
00:12:35,030 --> 00:12:36,240
I'll break your legs!

185
00:12:36,340 --> 00:12:37,010
Xiaoman!

186
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:39,360
Xiaoman, stop! Stop, Xiaoman!

187
00:12:39,750 --> 00:12:40,790
Don't ride the motorcycle.

188
00:12:40,790 --> 00:12:42,390
It closed down. Went out of business.

189
00:12:42,390 --> 00:12:45,150
You're back. Why didn't you say anything?

190
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:46,790
What's wrong, Xiaoman? Stand up straight.

191
00:12:46,790 --> 00:12:49,510
Did you wear the sweater
I knitted for you?

192
00:12:49,510 --> 00:12:51,030
I know you want to recite too.

193
00:12:51,030 --> 00:12:53,270
I'll let you do it. Bro, take it.

194
00:12:53,390 --> 00:12:55,270
My grandson managed to get me tickets.

195
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:56,870
Let's go watch the show.

196
00:12:56,870 --> 00:12:59,670
I want to watch my grandson perform too.

197
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:19,120
Da.

198
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:21,670
What brings you here?

199
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:23,800
I just fixed up the bike for you at home.

200
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:24,750
What's up?

201
00:13:24,910 --> 00:13:25,600
It's all yours.

202
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:26,840
Why are you returning it?

203
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:27,870
The way I am now...

204
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:30,570
With my state lately, I can't ride.

205
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,000
Riding it

206
00:13:32,430 --> 00:13:35,080
is faster and not as tiring.

207
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:36,860
Isn't it better than what you ride now?

208
00:13:36,860 --> 00:13:37,720
Let me tell you,

209
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:39,600
this is my proper gear now.

210
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,360
It saves gas

211
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:42,510
and gives me a workout.

212
00:13:42,510 --> 00:13:44,240
I can save money
and carry more passengers.

213
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,480
Why wouldn't I use it?

214
00:13:46,790 --> 00:13:48,390
Come on. Give me a hand.

215
00:13:48,790 --> 00:13:49,440
Be careful.

216
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,550
Let me bring it up for you. Here.

217
00:13:50,550 --> 00:13:51,600
One, two, go!

218
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,270
Alright.

219
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,500
Okay, I'm leaving.

220
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:02,020
I rely on this to look cool now.

221
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:32,770
Xiaoman.

222
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,080
Xiaoman!

223
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,630
He's not answering.

224
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:47,840
Xiaoman.

225
00:14:51,850 --> 00:14:52,490
Xiaoman.

226
00:14:54,210 --> 00:14:55,140
You scared me.

227
00:14:55,430 --> 00:14:56,830
I thought I was dreaming.

228
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,320
Seriously.

229
00:14:58,390 --> 00:14:59,480
How did you know I was back?

230
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,440
I heard it from...

231
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:01,790
from Mrs. Ding.

232
00:15:02,630 --> 00:15:05,360
You didn't even take off
your shoes to sleep.

233
00:15:05,630 --> 00:15:07,240
No, I often got up
to open the door at night,

234
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,670
so I thought
I wouldn't bother taking them off.

235
00:15:09,670 --> 00:15:10,750
Well... you...

236
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:12,550
Who came at night? Who was it?

237
00:15:12,610 --> 00:15:13,150
No.

238
00:15:13,180 --> 00:15:13,980
I heard wrong.

239
00:15:14,610 --> 00:15:15,570
I must have misheard to open the door.

240
00:15:15,570 --> 00:15:16,770
Are you feeling okay?

241
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:18,620
No. It's just that yesterday,

242
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,000
I didn't...

243
00:15:20,790 --> 00:15:21,910
sleep very well.

244
00:15:22,230 --> 00:15:23,210
I'm fine. I'm fine.

245
00:15:23,210 --> 00:15:24,740
Everything is fine at home?

246
00:15:25,910 --> 00:15:27,570
Your uncle knew you were back,

247
00:15:28,030 --> 00:15:29,390
so he made handmade noodles for you.

248
00:15:29,390 --> 00:15:31,630
I rushed over
because I was afraid they'd get soggy.

249
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:32,630
Eat up, come on.

250
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:42,130
Were you doing fine abroad?

251
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:47,750
Not as fine as home. Home is better.

252
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:51,630
Don't bother.

253
00:15:51,630 --> 00:15:52,600
I'll get it myself.

254
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:53,400
I'll go get it.

255
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,510
It's fine. I don't want vinegar.

256
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:56,710
I'll eat it like this.

257
00:15:57,270 --> 00:15:59,000
I'll go get a bottle of vinegar.

258
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:04,970
I didn't buy vinegar.

259
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:07,430
I haven't bought anything
since I came back.

260
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:25,640
What?

261
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:28,120
Nothing. I just love watching you eat
with such appetite.

262
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,980
It makes me happy to watch you eat.

263
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:41,660
What's wrong? What are you looking for?

264
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:43,660
Nothing. Who's knocking? Who is it?

265
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:45,100
Is nobody there?

266
00:16:47,390 --> 00:16:49,240
Maybe the neighbor's kids were bored,

267
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:51,970
so they came to prank me
in the middle of the night.

268
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:05,480
These are clothes I brought
for Uncle and you.

269
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:07,829
No rush. No rush.

270
00:17:07,829 --> 00:17:08,690
There's no bag.

271
00:17:09,550 --> 00:17:11,510
Look at you, still thinking of us.

272
00:17:11,510 --> 00:17:12,589
Hurry and finish eating first.

273
00:17:12,589 --> 00:17:13,160
Right.

274
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:17,550
Clothes, pants, and what else is there?

275
00:17:19,349 --> 00:17:21,829
Just these.
Please take them back to Uncle.

276
00:17:27,109 --> 00:17:29,160
How many days have you been back?

277
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:31,500
I just got back.

278
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:32,470
I came back

279
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:34,510
and stayed home for one day.

280
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:37,510
Then I went to my mentor's house.

281
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:40,440
If you're feeling unwell or anything,

282
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:42,200
you have to tell me.

283
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,480
Nothing. I'm fine.

284
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:45,550
Look at me, I'm in great shape now.

285
00:17:49,790 --> 00:17:50,590
Xiaoman.

286
00:17:52,310 --> 00:17:53,350
Look at you.

287
00:17:55,750 --> 00:17:56,440
Xiaoman.

288
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:03,480
Are you okay?

289
00:18:05,110 --> 00:18:06,790
No, Auntie, why are you here?

290
00:18:06,790 --> 00:18:08,340
I was worried about you.

291
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:09,790
Since you came back,

292
00:18:09,790 --> 00:18:11,320
you've looked so listless.

293
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:13,160
I was afraid you might be sick.

294
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:14,560
Are you not feeling well?

295
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:15,880
No, I'm not.

296
00:18:16,230 --> 00:18:17,110
Hello, Xiaoman.

297
00:18:17,110 --> 00:18:18,310
This is Ms. Zhang.

298
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:20,390
Alright, I'll be straight with you.

299
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:23,050
Ms. Zhang is the Director
at our plant hospital.

300
00:18:23,270 --> 00:18:25,200
I brought her here to check you out.

301
00:18:25,790 --> 00:18:26,590
No need.

302
00:18:27,350 --> 00:18:28,680
I-I-I really...

303
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,350
Tell us where it hurts.

304
00:18:30,350 --> 00:18:31,270
You have to speak up.

305
00:18:31,270 --> 00:18:32,470
How do I explain this?

306
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:38,070
I... I keep hearing noises in my ears.

307
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:41,240
Sometimes it's talking,

308
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:43,030
sometimes cars, sometimes other things.

309
00:18:43,030 --> 00:18:44,070
It's all a mess.

310
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:46,030
Is it continuous,

311
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:47,230
or does it come and go?

312
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:47,920
It comes and goes.

313
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:49,160
Sometimes it's very sudden,

314
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:50,720
like a sudden bang

315
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:51,750
or a sudden noise.

316
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,630
What... what does that mean?

317
00:18:54,630 --> 00:18:57,960
Did anything happen
before these hallucinations started?

318
00:18:58,310 --> 00:18:59,030
I just...

319
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:01,680
fell into the sea.

320
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:03,110
I almost drowned.

321
00:19:03,110 --> 00:19:06,590
My ears haven't been right
since I woke up.

322
00:19:06,630 --> 00:19:08,190
Let's do a check-up then.

323
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:09,880
Why didn't you tell us?

324
00:19:09,880 --> 00:19:11,160
Why keep it from the family?

325
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:12,000
I'm fine.

326
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:14,310
Look, I'm fine now.

327
00:19:14,330 --> 00:19:16,500
I didn't want you to worry about me.

328
00:19:17,310 --> 00:19:18,030
I remember

329
00:19:18,030 --> 00:19:20,110
he fell into the water when he was young.

330
00:19:20,110 --> 00:19:21,420
He almost drowned.

331
00:19:23,030 --> 00:19:25,270
His ear looks normal inside.
Nothing's wrong.

332
00:19:25,270 --> 00:19:27,480
I suspect Xiaoman has PTSD.

333
00:19:29,150 --> 00:19:30,300
What D?

334
00:19:30,840 --> 00:19:31,830
PTSD

335
00:19:31,830 --> 00:19:33,890
is Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder.

336
00:19:33,990 --> 00:19:37,060
He needs to go to Anning Hospital
for a detailed checkup immediately

337
00:19:37,060 --> 00:19:37,960
and get hospitalization.

338
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:39,720
Why go to Anning Hospital?

339
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,570
Isn't that for a psycho?

340
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:42,440
PTSD

341
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:44,200
is also a kind of mental illness.

342
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,640
Don't feel pressured.

343
00:19:46,450 --> 00:19:48,580
We should listen to the doctor.

344
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:50,270
Then go there

345
00:19:50,270 --> 00:19:51,240
to get checked for peace of mind.

346
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:52,980
I don't think it's a serious problem.

347
00:19:52,980 --> 00:19:54,590
Okay. I'll go

348
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:55,650
in a couple of days.

349
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:09,980
There's something I want to tell you.

350
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:13,100
I have an opportunity
to study abroad in France.

351
00:20:14,070 --> 00:20:16,200
What if I don't come back for 2 years?

352
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:19,160
What if I go to other countries?

353
00:20:20,130 --> 00:20:22,720
What if I travel the world?

354
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,330
What are you doing? Watch the road!

355
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:43,610
[Clinical Psychology]
[Anning Hospital Inpatient Department]

356
00:20:48,070 --> 00:20:49,750
I... I nearly drowned.

357
00:20:52,830 --> 00:20:54,490
I fell... fell into the water.

358
00:20:54,830 --> 00:20:57,350
Ever since,
my ears have started making noises.

359
00:20:57,350 --> 00:20:58,720
At first, I did not

360
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:00,000
take it seriously.

361
00:21:00,110 --> 00:21:01,200
But later...

362
00:21:01,510 --> 00:21:03,440
I kept hearing someone calling me,

363
00:21:03,790 --> 00:21:04,750
knocking on the door,

364
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:07,070
and all kinds of random noises.

365
00:21:07,310 --> 00:21:08,880
Sometimes I run away. Sometimes,

366
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:09,550
I can't sleep as well.

367
00:21:09,550 --> 00:21:11,240
Once it gets to night,

368
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:12,900
it just keeps buzzing in here.

369
00:21:12,910 --> 00:21:14,800
I simply... simply can't sleep.

370
00:21:14,830 --> 00:21:16,200
Recently, when I go out,

371
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:17,480
I can't tell what's real anymore.

372
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:19,420
The noises are various.

373
00:21:19,450 --> 00:21:21,660
Sometimes cars, sometimes voices.

374
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:24,080
It doesn't even let me cross the street.

375
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:26,670
I thought I'd better hurry to the hospital
to check it out.

376
00:21:26,670 --> 00:21:28,340
I can't go on like this.

377
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:31,440
How can anyone stand

378
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:32,840
not sleeping for so long?

379
00:21:33,110 --> 00:21:34,240
Your current symptoms

380
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:35,170
are very severe.

381
00:21:35,310 --> 00:21:37,040
I'll write you a checklist now.

382
00:21:37,110 --> 00:21:38,310
Go get checked first.

383
00:21:38,890 --> 00:21:39,950
Let's check it out.

384
00:21:41,630 --> 00:21:42,110
Here.

385
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:43,680
Go pay the fee.

386
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:47,350
So many tests?

387
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:48,680
Your condition

388
00:21:48,790 --> 00:21:49,830
is very complex.

389
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,710
You need a comprehensive checkup.

390
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:53,910
We can only admit you after a diagnosis.

391
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:55,400
Also, let me tell you,

392
00:21:55,510 --> 00:21:56,880
your two near-drowning incidents,

393
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:58,390
no matter how far apart they were,

394
00:21:58,390 --> 00:22:00,430
are a trigger for your condition.

395
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:05,270
A trigger factor. A trigger.

396
00:22:07,070 --> 00:22:08,130
Do you understand?

397
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,240
Urban management officers are here!

398
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,830
Urban management officers are here!

399
00:22:13,830 --> 00:22:14,750
Let's go! Go!

400
00:22:15,510 --> 00:22:17,270
Let's go! Go!

401
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,240
Stop right there! Don't run!

402
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,010
I told you
setting up stalls isn't allowed,

403
00:22:24,010 --> 00:22:25,270
yet here you are again!

404
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,060
Stand there, Ding.

405
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:29,150
Stop running.

406
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:31,680
Ding.

407
00:22:31,870 --> 00:22:33,400
Stand there! Quit running!

408
00:22:34,480 --> 00:22:35,070
Halt, Ding.

409
00:22:35,070 --> 00:22:36,240
Come here, Ding.

410
00:22:36,270 --> 00:22:38,330
Stop. Come here. Stop running. Come.

411
00:22:41,790 --> 00:22:42,640
Ding,

412
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:45,590
you're too old to be running
for your life like that.

413
00:22:45,590 --> 00:22:47,050
Watch out for your safety.

414
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:48,610
It's my first day...

415
00:22:48,850 --> 00:22:50,850
my first day setting up a stall here.

416
00:22:51,230 --> 00:22:53,240
I didn't know vending wasn't allowed here.

417
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:54,680
I'll leave now, okay?

418
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:55,330
I'll leave now.

419
00:22:55,330 --> 00:22:56,330
First day out?

420
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:59,220
Then who made that oil mess
on the ground over there?

421
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,400
That couldn't be me.

422
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,830
I grill chicken ribs.

423
00:23:01,830 --> 00:23:03,070
There's barely any meat on them.

424
00:23:03,070 --> 00:23:04,270
How could there be grease?

425
00:23:04,270 --> 00:23:05,680
How many times have I said this?

426
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,660
The station square
is the face of the city.

427
00:23:07,660 --> 00:23:08,380
Yes.

428
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:09,750
No vending allowed.

429
00:23:09,750 --> 00:23:10,590
Yes, yes.

430
00:23:10,590 --> 00:23:11,830
I'm confiscating your cart.

431
00:23:11,830 --> 00:23:12,720
No, no, don't, please.

432
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:13,200
Here.

433
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:14,240
No way, don't do this.

434
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:14,920
Hongtashan cigarettes.

435
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:15,830
Don't give me that. I don't smoke.

436
00:23:15,830 --> 00:23:16,230
Good cigarettes.

437
00:23:16,230 --> 00:23:17,350
I'm confiscating this cart.

438
00:23:17,350 --> 00:23:18,480
No, you can't. Please don't.

439
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:19,640
Let go. Let go right now.

440
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:20,480
If you don't,

441
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:22,490
I'll call the police
for joint enforcement.

442
00:23:22,490 --> 00:23:23,990
Then it won't just be your cart seized.

443
00:23:23,990 --> 00:23:25,200
They'll take you in too.

444
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:26,200
Have a smoke and calm down first.

445
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,300
I don't smoke. I don't smoke.

446
00:23:27,300 --> 00:23:28,800
Wait, so where do I go
to get my cart back?

447
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:30,060
What are you thinking?

448
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:31,310
The cart is confiscated,

449
00:23:31,310 --> 00:23:32,640
not temporarily detained.

450
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:33,880
So you just take it,
and I'll never get it back?

451
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:34,440
Yes.

452
00:23:36,030 --> 00:23:36,510
Come on.

453
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:37,060
Come on!

454
00:23:37,310 --> 00:23:37,790
Come on!

455
00:23:38,590 --> 00:23:39,960
Just run me over! Come on!

456
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:41,310
Are you trying
to starve the common people?

457
00:23:41,310 --> 00:23:43,310
Get up and let's talk this out, okay?

458
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:44,200
No use!

459
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:45,030
Come on, get up.

460
00:23:45,030 --> 00:23:46,160
You try touching me!

461
00:23:47,460 --> 00:23:48,220
Who are you?

462
00:23:51,050 --> 00:23:51,980
What do you want?

463
00:24:07,090 --> 00:24:08,270
You little brat...

464
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:11,880
why didn't you tell me
you were coming back?

465
00:24:12,230 --> 00:24:13,560
How do you know I'm here?

466
00:24:13,830 --> 00:24:15,070
Mrs. Ding told me.

467
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:17,230
Come on. Let go.

468
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:18,980
Let's go home. Come on.

469
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:22,350
I'm confiscating your cart!

470
00:24:24,900 --> 00:24:25,760
It's all yours.

471
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,590
My wife made this... I can't...

472
00:24:28,590 --> 00:24:29,400
Hey, push the cart away.

473
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,400
The cart, don't you want it back?

474
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,530
Who cares? Leave it.

475
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:32,480
Let's go home!

476
00:24:36,900 --> 00:24:38,500
Wait. I'll get a case of beer.

477
00:24:38,990 --> 00:24:40,990
Ma'am, I'll take a case of Snow Beer.

478
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:42,480
It's still 1.5 a bottle, right?

479
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:42,930
Right.

480
00:24:42,950 --> 00:24:43,630
33 yuan?

481
00:24:45,110 --> 00:24:46,070
Business was slow today.

482
00:24:46,070 --> 00:24:46,680
I'm 3 yuan short.

483
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:48,480
I'll pay you
when I return the bottles tomorrow.

484
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:49,000
It's fine.

485
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,270
Let's go home, alright?

486
00:24:50,270 --> 00:24:51,480
We'll go back tomorrow.

487
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:52,880
Now that the cart is gone,

488
00:24:53,840 --> 00:24:54,770
let's just quit.

489
00:24:54,830 --> 00:24:56,630
We can find something else to do.

490
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:57,680
Is it heavy?

491
00:24:58,200 --> 00:24:58,750
No.

492
00:24:59,110 --> 00:24:59,680
Not bad.

493
00:24:59,830 --> 00:25:00,920
You're still in good shape.

494
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:02,650
I heard that companies in Japan

495
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:03,880
don't treat workers like humans.

496
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:05,350
They use them like machines.

497
00:25:05,350 --> 00:25:06,070
No.

498
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:11,550
Why are you spitting out
one word at a time?

499
00:25:11,550 --> 00:25:13,080
Don't people talk in Japan?

500
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:17,440
There's a language barrier there,

501
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:20,030
and I couldn't learn the language.

502
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:22,590
Mr. Ding, where is your place?

503
00:25:22,590 --> 00:25:23,240
Right here.

504
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:24,510
Here. We're here. Look.

505
00:25:24,510 --> 00:25:25,480
It's steaming.

506
00:25:26,250 --> 00:25:26,840
I'm back!

507
00:25:27,070 --> 00:25:28,130
You're back, Ding.

508
00:25:28,310 --> 00:25:29,100
Who is this?

509
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:30,240
Didn't I tell you about him?

510
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,480
My apprentice from Japan.

511
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:33,440
He came to see me as soon as he got back.

512
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:33,960
Go on, Xiaoman.

513
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:35,890
Cool this beer down with tap water.

514
00:25:36,110 --> 00:25:36,750
Alright, I'll take him.

515
00:25:36,750 --> 00:25:37,480
You take him.

516
00:25:37,750 --> 00:25:38,400
Over here.

517
00:25:53,010 --> 00:25:55,640
Buddy. Did you come back from Japan?

518
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:58,000
Yes.

519
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:58,440
Let me tell you,

520
00:25:58,440 --> 00:26:00,570
your mentor talks about you every day.

521
00:26:05,790 --> 00:26:06,830
Let me walk around.

522
00:26:06,830 --> 00:26:08,160
You sleep in this room?

523
00:26:08,660 --> 00:26:09,920
It's huge. A big villa.

524
00:26:09,930 --> 00:26:11,330
-Let me see.
-A big villa.

525
00:26:19,790 --> 00:26:20,590
Sir.

526
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:23,310
Where does my mentor sleep?

527
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:27,200
He sleeps on the edge of the kang.

528
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:29,000
Here?

529
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:30,920
Your mentor

530
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:32,430
finishes work quite late.

531
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:34,740
He's afraid of disturbing our sleep,

532
00:26:34,750 --> 00:26:36,080
so he sleeps on the edge.

533
00:26:36,310 --> 00:26:38,270
Even though he sleeps
at the end of the kang,

534
00:26:38,270 --> 00:26:40,270
we heat it up well in winter,

535
00:26:40,590 --> 00:26:41,650
so he won't freeze.

536
00:26:41,980 --> 00:26:42,500
Okay.

537
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:44,440
Well,

538
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:46,770
thank you all
for taking care of my mentor.

539
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:48,270
We're all away from home.

540
00:26:48,270 --> 00:26:50,000
It's normal to help each other.

541
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,030
Your mentor's wife comes by often

542
00:26:51,030 --> 00:26:52,030
to help us tidy up.

543
00:26:53,110 --> 00:26:53,840
That's good.

544
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:56,110
Xiaoman!

545
00:26:56,270 --> 00:26:56,960
Yes?

546
00:26:57,350 --> 00:26:58,480
Come out and help me.

547
00:26:59,270 --> 00:27:00,070
I'll do it.

548
00:27:00,790 --> 00:27:03,520
I love asking for your help
as soon as you're back.

549
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:05,330
What do you need?

550
00:27:05,830 --> 00:27:06,590
Get me some charcoal.

551
00:27:06,590 --> 00:27:07,790
It's in a small basin.

552
00:27:10,830 --> 00:27:12,230
Wow, there's a stove too.

553
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:16,830
Business was good a couple of years ago,

554
00:27:16,830 --> 00:27:18,230
so I bought an extra stove

555
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,310
and put it away.

556
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:22,510
I haven't used it this year.
Business has been slow.

557
00:27:22,510 --> 00:27:23,920
Luckily, business has been slow,

558
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,580
or this would be confiscated.

559
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,790
Otherwise,
you wouldn't be eating this today.

560
00:27:27,790 --> 00:27:28,520
Smells good.

561
00:27:29,510 --> 00:27:30,350
I'm back!

562
00:27:31,350 --> 00:27:32,240
-Where did you go?
-The food is ready!

563
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,310
The food is here.

564
00:27:33,510 --> 00:27:34,310
Hurry up.

565
00:27:34,750 --> 00:27:35,550
We're all set.

566
00:27:36,070 --> 00:27:37,000
The beer is here. Great.

567
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:37,550
Come on. Come on.

568
00:27:37,550 --> 00:27:38,720
Find a bottle opener.

569
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:39,370
Leave it.

570
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:42,550
I asked him to get some snacks for me.

571
00:27:42,550 --> 00:27:43,550
You paid for them?

572
00:27:44,310 --> 00:27:44,960
Why waste it?

573
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:47,360
We have chicken ribs.
Why buy other snacks?

574
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:48,270
Ding!

575
00:27:48,510 --> 00:27:49,640
You jerk!

576
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:50,640
Get the hell out here!

577
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:51,550
Turn this over for me.

578
00:27:51,550 --> 00:27:52,000
Turn it over.

579
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:52,790
How many times have I told you?

580
00:27:52,790 --> 00:27:53,920
Don't grill those chicken ribs inside!

581
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:55,240
It's getting smoky in here.

582
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:56,070
Why don't you ever learn?

583
00:27:56,070 --> 00:27:57,030
Okay, okay.

584
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:58,730
-I…
-You're out of line!

585
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:00,830
My apprentice from Japan came back.

586
00:28:00,830 --> 00:28:01,680
I'm just grilling for today.

587
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:02,880
I won't do it tomorrow, okay?

588
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:04,030
I don't care about
your Japanese apprentice,

589
00:28:04,030 --> 00:28:04,720
American apprentice,

590
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:05,510
or Philippine apprentice.

591
00:28:05,510 --> 00:28:06,920
What does that have to do with me?

592
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:07,550
My goodness,

593
00:28:07,550 --> 00:28:09,730
you sure have a lot of connections.

594
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:11,160
I have to say,

595
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:13,070
with your shabby chicken rib cart,

596
00:28:13,070 --> 00:28:14,790
it's oily and smoky every day.

597
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:15,720
It's smoky everywhere.

598
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:16,830
What do you want?

599
00:28:17,110 --> 00:28:19,200
If you set the house on fire,
what should I do?

600
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:20,200
What should I do then?

601
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:21,790
I won't. I'm just grilling once.

602
00:28:21,790 --> 00:28:22,790
If I grill again tomorrow,

603
00:28:22,790 --> 00:28:23,880
I don't need you to drive me away,

604
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:24,310
okay?

605
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:25,160
Let me tell you,

606
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:26,880
I'll trust you for the last time.

607
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:27,270
Done.

608
00:28:27,270 --> 00:28:28,240
Don't you feel ashamed?

609
00:28:28,240 --> 00:28:29,000
I surely do.

610
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:30,030
Go, come on.

611
00:28:30,030 --> 00:28:31,200
So annoying.

612
00:28:34,700 --> 00:28:35,350
Let's eat.

613
00:28:35,510 --> 00:28:36,270
These are ready.

614
00:28:36,270 --> 00:28:38,160
We'll grill more after we finish eating.

615
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:39,310
-I'm so lucky today.
-Have a seat.

616
00:28:39,310 --> 00:28:40,240
The skewers are ready.

617
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:40,880
Here.

618
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:42,850
I'll have one first.

619
00:28:44,590 --> 00:28:45,150
Oh my god.

620
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:46,030
Mr. Ding.

621
00:28:46,830 --> 00:28:48,700
Take small sips. What are you doing?

622
00:28:48,700 --> 00:28:50,560
-Ding's really happy.
-Mr. Ding.

623
00:28:51,830 --> 00:28:52,560
Impressive.

624
00:28:53,650 --> 00:28:54,710
You drank too fast.

625
00:28:55,150 --> 00:28:55,890
I'm happy today.

626
00:28:55,890 --> 00:28:56,750
Eat the chicken ribs.

627
00:28:56,750 --> 00:28:57,880
They taste amazing.

628
00:28:58,270 --> 00:28:59,070
Come on, have a drink.

629
00:28:59,070 --> 00:29:02,000
You're acting like
it's your first time eating this.

630
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:08,500
Mr. Ding, I'm going to the back...

631
00:29:09,550 --> 00:29:10,590
to use the toilet.

632
00:29:24,700 --> 00:29:25,260
Sit.

633
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:35,400
Speak.

634
00:29:38,350 --> 00:29:39,110
About what?

635
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:40,500
Zhang Xiaoman.

636
00:29:41,790 --> 00:29:43,720
I raised you since you were little.

637
00:29:44,640 --> 00:29:45,440
I know exactly what you're thinking

638
00:29:45,440 --> 00:29:46,880
before you even do it.

639
00:29:47,270 --> 00:29:50,070
You've been acting strange
all the way here today.

640
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:52,330
What happened in Japan?

641
00:29:53,550 --> 00:29:56,310
Nothing. I just worked all day.

642
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:00,460
Can work make you look this pathetic?

643
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:07,810
Does it have something to do with Xiaodan?

644
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:14,830
Xiaodan...

645
00:30:16,510 --> 00:30:17,910
Xiaodan broke up with me.

646
00:30:22,550 --> 00:30:23,810
I know you two broke up.

647
00:30:25,070 --> 00:30:27,270
Chief Engineer Yan told me everything.

648
00:30:29,510 --> 00:30:32,240
You don't come home
just because you two broke up?

649
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:34,680
Don't you know
my wife and I worry about you,

650
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:35,200
do you?

651
00:30:42,270 --> 00:30:43,440
Seeing you back today,

652
00:30:43,440 --> 00:30:45,030
I took a load off my mind.

653
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:49,750
I thought I shouldn't pry

654
00:30:50,480 --> 00:30:52,510
and should just wait for you to tell me.

655
00:30:52,510 --> 00:30:53,640
There's nothing we can't talk about.

656
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:54,270
But you,

657
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:57,320
you just clammed up on me.

658
00:30:59,160 --> 00:30:59,880
No.

659
00:31:01,590 --> 00:31:02,680
I was wrong. My bad.

660
00:31:02,680 --> 00:31:03,790
Wrong about what?

661
00:31:05,550 --> 00:31:08,080
Zhang Xiaoman,
when have you ever been wrong?

662
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:14,350
Before you went to Japan,

663
00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:15,480
what did you tell me?

664
00:31:16,270 --> 00:31:17,590
You said no matter what happened,

665
00:31:17,590 --> 00:31:18,800
you'd call me immediately.

666
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:19,930
I waited and waited.

667
00:31:22,270 --> 00:31:23,400
How long has it been?

668
00:31:26,590 --> 00:31:27,750
Not a single call.

669
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:30,800
Not even a single one.

670
00:31:31,550 --> 00:31:34,550
What? Were you waiting for me
to go to Japan to find you?

671
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:35,750
Let me tell you,

672
00:31:35,750 --> 00:31:36,750
if my pockets were deep,

673
00:31:36,750 --> 00:31:37,960
if I had any spare cash,

674
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:38,920
I would have rushed over there

675
00:31:38,920 --> 00:31:40,520
and dragged you back myself!

676
00:31:45,660 --> 00:31:46,750
Don't be mad, Mr. Ding.

677
00:31:46,750 --> 00:31:47,480
Back then...

678
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:51,030
I was young

679
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,440
and out of my mind.

680
00:31:53,550 --> 00:31:55,000
I was impulsive.

681
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:56,900
I just thought I should...

682
00:31:59,030 --> 00:32:00,690
should go out, make my own way,

683
00:32:01,790 --> 00:32:02,850
and find a place...

684
00:32:05,510 --> 00:32:06,830
I... I was wrong.

685
00:32:06,830 --> 00:32:07,640
I was wrong, Mr. Ding.

686
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:08,590
Don't be mad.

687
00:32:10,070 --> 00:32:12,330
You can't always just think of yourself.

688
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:16,040
Think about your family.

689
00:32:18,270 --> 00:32:19,670
We're worried about you.

690
00:32:45,150 --> 00:32:45,910
What is this?

691
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:49,640
I brought you a gift from Japan.

692
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:50,840
What is it?

693
00:32:51,070 --> 00:32:52,270
They say this works

694
00:32:53,990 --> 00:32:55,450
just like those shots you used to take.

695
00:32:55,450 --> 00:32:56,490
Get out of here.

696
00:32:59,530 --> 00:33:01,450
You look pretty healthy to me.

697
00:33:01,620 --> 00:33:03,550
Just take it. Put it in your pocket.

698
00:33:04,030 --> 00:33:04,730
What are you doing?

699
00:33:04,730 --> 00:33:05,380
Keep it.

700
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:10,090
Anyway, it's good to have you back.

701
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:11,830
I'm telling you again,

702
00:33:11,830 --> 00:33:12,920
don't keep things from me in the future.

703
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:13,590
Do you hear me?

704
00:33:13,590 --> 00:33:15,000
I know. Don't worry, Mr. Ding.

705
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:15,730
Don't worry.

706
00:33:17,920 --> 00:33:19,980
How many pills should I take at a time?

707
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:23,110
I'll check online when I get back.

708
00:33:23,110 --> 00:33:24,590
I can't read these characters either.

709
00:33:24,590 --> 00:33:26,270
Why is this all in Japanese?

710
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:31,060
Put it away safely.

711
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:33,810
Don't tell my wife.

712
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:35,510
Let's go back to finish the drink.

713
00:33:35,510 --> 00:33:36,570
Let's go. Let's go.

714
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:38,240
What is this good stuff?

715
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:39,000
Some pills.

716
00:33:39,740 --> 00:33:40,750
Come on, down one.

717
00:33:40,750 --> 00:33:41,830
Come on. Come on.

718
00:33:42,310 --> 00:33:43,030
Okay. Okay.

719
00:33:43,070 --> 00:33:43,480
Okay.

720
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:47,820
Sing a song?

721
00:33:48,030 --> 00:33:48,550
Great, great.

722
00:33:48,550 --> 00:33:49,070
Sing one.

723
00:33:49,070 --> 00:33:49,960
Come on, sing one.

724
00:33:49,960 --> 00:33:50,490
Sing one.

725
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:51,830
Sing along if you know the words.

726
00:33:51,830 --> 00:33:52,310
Okay.

727
00:33:52,310 --> 00:33:54,270
We gotta enrich our leisure lives.

728
00:33:54,270 --> 00:33:55,070
-Okay.
-Okay.

729
00:33:56,440 --> 00:34:01,680
♪ The eldest brother is always young ♪

730
00:34:01,750 --> 00:34:06,960
♪ He's like a pine tree,
evergreen in winter and summer ♪

731
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:11,960
♪ He's not afraid of wind and rain ♪

732
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:17,150
♪ He fears not the bitter cold
and freezing frost ♪

733
00:34:17,150 --> 00:34:21,840
♪ He does not waver or move ♪

734
00:34:21,960 --> 00:34:25,960
♪ Standing on the top of the mountain
forever ♪

735
00:34:25,960 --> 00:34:26,710
One more time.

736
00:34:26,710 --> 00:34:31,630
♪ The eldest brother is always young ♪

737
00:34:31,630 --> 00:34:36,630
♪ He's like a pine tree,
evergreen in winter and summer ♪

738
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:41,920
♪ He's not afraid of wind and rain ♪

739
00:34:42,230 --> 00:34:46,070
♪ He fears not the bitter cold
and freezing frost ♪

740
00:34:53,110 --> 00:34:53,960
Xiaoman?

741
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:55,630
Oh my god.

742
00:34:56,190 --> 00:34:57,590
My goodness, why are you back from Japan?

743
00:34:57,590 --> 00:34:58,550
Come in, come in.

744
00:34:58,550 --> 00:34:59,150
Sit, sit.

745
00:34:59,590 --> 00:35:02,190
Sit here. It really is you.
I was wondering.

746
00:35:02,350 --> 00:35:03,010
Have a seat.

747
00:35:03,460 --> 00:35:04,390
Have some seeds.

748
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:07,330
My god, why are you back from Japan?

749
00:35:09,510 --> 00:35:11,170
Did you get transferred to HR?

750
00:35:12,030 --> 00:35:13,400
Weren't you in Finance?

751
00:35:13,920 --> 00:35:15,320
They merged ages ago.

752
00:35:15,710 --> 00:35:17,960
Now HR is Finance too.

753
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:19,760
And the old Labor Department

754
00:35:19,760 --> 00:35:20,760
was merged as well.

755
00:35:20,760 --> 00:35:21,960
I'm the only one left.

756
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:23,590
Just you?

757
00:35:25,510 --> 00:35:26,230
I don't know

758
00:35:26,230 --> 00:35:27,920
how much longer I'll be working here.

759
00:35:27,920 --> 00:35:28,320
Here.

760
00:35:28,340 --> 00:35:30,470
What about the others? What do they do?

761
00:35:30,990 --> 00:35:31,840
What others?

762
00:35:32,190 --> 00:35:34,550
Where did everyone else go?

763
00:35:34,630 --> 00:35:35,800
Our old classmates?

764
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:39,760
Our classmates are just getting by.

765
00:35:40,110 --> 00:35:43,030
Some are doing odd jobs to make money,

766
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:45,510
setting up street stalls
to sell grilled corn,

767
00:35:45,510 --> 00:35:46,960
grilled fish fillets,
and things like that.

768
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:47,710
And some

769
00:35:47,710 --> 00:35:50,770
have gone to Tiecheng
or Shenyang to start businesses.

770
00:35:51,590 --> 00:35:53,400
There are some
I can't even contact anymore.

771
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:55,190
Some have gone south,

772
00:35:55,190 --> 00:35:56,920
while others have gone abroad.

773
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:02,070
Right, by the way...

774
00:36:03,970 --> 00:36:05,030
Baldy Song is gone.

775
00:36:09,900 --> 00:36:11,100
What happened to him?

776
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:13,590
He was different from us.

777
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:17,290
He was assigned to the plant office
right after graduation.

778
00:36:17,630 --> 00:36:19,110
I heard, just rumors,

779
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:23,190
that he was drinking with clients,
had too much,

780
00:36:23,740 --> 00:36:25,540
and choked to death right there.

781
00:36:25,650 --> 00:36:27,180
While he was throwing up...

782
00:36:32,230 --> 00:36:33,580
Why would he do that?

783
00:36:35,290 --> 00:36:37,690
Look at you, back from your trip abroad,

784
00:36:38,190 --> 00:36:39,480
you look good.

785
00:36:40,550 --> 00:36:42,000
I... I came here just...

786
00:36:43,150 --> 00:36:44,440
I just want to ask...

787
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:47,970
Isn't my personnel file
still with the plant?

788
00:36:48,430 --> 00:36:50,140
So for someone like me,

789
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:53,230
how do I get reimbursed?

790
00:36:53,250 --> 00:36:54,040
Reimbursed?

791
00:36:54,620 --> 00:36:56,960
You just got back from Japan;
what are you reimbursing?

792
00:36:56,960 --> 00:36:59,800
We can't reimburse expenses from Japan.

793
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:00,760
No.

794
00:37:01,510 --> 00:37:02,400
Not from Japan.

795
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:05,400
I might need to claim some expenses
in a couple of days.

796
00:37:05,710 --> 00:37:06,630
Well...

797
00:37:09,070 --> 00:37:09,880
You know...

798
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:13,320
Claim some medical expenses.

799
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:13,580
I...

800
00:37:13,610 --> 00:37:14,240
Medical expenses?

801
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:14,960
I'm sick.

802
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:15,550
Well.

803
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:16,360
Oh my god.

804
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:17,800
Why are you sick?

805
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:19,480
Why didn't you say so earlier?

806
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:21,610
God, I was just chatting about others.

807
00:37:22,750 --> 00:37:24,710
What does this mean?
What's wrong with you?

808
00:37:24,710 --> 00:37:27,230
I asked our plant hospital.

809
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:29,010
They can't treat it.

810
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:32,840
They told me to go to Anning Hospital
for medicine.

811
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:34,040
To get treated there.

812
00:37:34,190 --> 00:37:34,910
I was wondering,

813
00:37:34,910 --> 00:37:37,370
how do I get reimbursed
for Anning Hospital?

814
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:41,400
Xiaoman, we're old classmates.

815
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:42,360
Regarding your request,

816
00:37:42,360 --> 00:37:44,490
I'll definitely try to prioritize it.

817
00:37:44,510 --> 00:37:46,040
But I'll be honest with you.

818
00:37:46,400 --> 00:37:48,710
You've seen the situation at the plant.

819
00:37:49,130 --> 00:37:51,110
There really isn't much money
in the account.

820
00:37:51,110 --> 00:37:53,000
Look at those reimbursement forms
over there.

821
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:55,110
There's a whole stack of them
sitting there.

822
00:37:55,110 --> 00:37:56,480
Those old patients in the plant

823
00:37:56,480 --> 00:37:59,070
all paid out of their own pockets first.

824
00:37:59,510 --> 00:38:01,320
If you ask me, why don't you

825
00:38:01,590 --> 00:38:02,840
pay for it yourself first?

826
00:38:02,840 --> 00:38:03,710
We can reimburse it later.

827
00:38:03,710 --> 00:38:04,770
Let's take it slow.

828
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:06,510
Okay?

829
00:38:08,190 --> 00:38:08,760
Okay.

830
00:38:09,180 --> 00:38:09,750
Okay.

831
00:38:10,030 --> 00:38:12,030
Wait, but what are your symptoms?

832
00:38:15,030 --> 00:38:18,670
Actually, as for symptoms,
it's nothing much.

833
00:38:18,670 --> 00:38:20,730
Just some auditory hallucinations.

834
00:38:20,760 --> 00:38:22,290
Auditory hallucinations?

835
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:25,920
Lulu, have you heard?

836
00:38:26,070 --> 00:38:27,730
What's wrong? What happened?

837
00:38:28,110 --> 00:38:29,110
Isn't this Xiaoman?

838
00:38:29,110 --> 00:38:30,510
When did you get back?

839
00:38:31,070 --> 00:38:32,430
I just got back.

840
00:38:33,190 --> 00:38:35,400
Have you seen your mentor
since you got back?

841
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:36,150
Yes.

842
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:38,070
Well...

843
00:38:38,070 --> 00:38:38,550
What's wrong?

844
00:38:38,550 --> 00:38:41,510
I heard something happened to Mr. Ding
just now.

845
00:38:41,510 --> 00:38:42,480
The police even came.

846
00:38:42,480 --> 00:38:43,940
What happened to Mr. Ding?

847
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:45,110
I don't know the details.

848
00:38:45,110 --> 00:38:45,550
Wait.

849
00:38:45,550 --> 00:38:46,510
Where did it happen?

850
00:38:46,510 --> 00:38:47,440
At the main gate.

851
00:38:47,590 --> 00:38:49,050
Near the security office.

852
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:54,150
Ding, you're getting on in years.

853
00:38:54,150 --> 00:38:55,750
Why do you love making a fuss?

854
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:58,920
Why did you hang your banner
on the street lamp?

855
00:38:59,110 --> 00:39:01,030
I've said it so many times. It wasn't...

856
00:39:01,030 --> 00:39:02,150
It wasn't me.

857
00:39:02,590 --> 00:39:03,440
It wasn't you?

858
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:04,400
Seriously?

859
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:06,030
That banner clearly says,

860
00:39:06,030 --> 00:39:07,550
"Ding's Grilled Chicken Ribs."

861
00:39:07,550 --> 00:39:08,190
How many Dings

862
00:39:08,190 --> 00:39:09,630
sell grilled chicken ribs around here?

863
00:39:09,630 --> 00:39:11,440
I woke up and found my banner stolen.

864
00:39:11,440 --> 00:39:12,320
I even wanted to call the police.

865
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:13,590
Ding, let me remind you.

866
00:39:13,590 --> 00:39:15,630
Don't think you can get away with this.

867
00:39:15,630 --> 00:39:17,230
Leniency to those who confess,
severity to those who resist.

868
00:39:17,230 --> 00:39:17,960
You know the drill.

869
00:39:17,960 --> 00:39:19,800
Leng, y-you know me.

870
00:39:19,800 --> 00:39:20,590
I...

871
00:39:20,590 --> 00:39:22,000
I'm sitting right here.

872
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:22,570
You know what kind of person I am,

873
00:39:22,570 --> 00:39:24,380
don't you?

874
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:28,300
Maybe someone else really did it?

875
00:39:28,550 --> 00:39:29,070
Look.

876
00:39:30,670 --> 00:39:31,320
Captain.

877
00:39:31,550 --> 00:39:32,590
Someone's turning themselves in.

878
00:39:32,590 --> 00:39:33,240
Who?

879
00:39:34,510 --> 00:39:35,070
Me.

880
00:39:38,190 --> 00:39:39,230
What are you doing?

881
00:39:39,230 --> 00:39:40,490
You go out first, Ding.

882
00:39:40,550 --> 00:39:41,110
No, you...

883
00:39:41,110 --> 00:39:42,360
I told you to get out!

884
00:39:43,510 --> 00:39:44,360
There's a stool here.

885
00:39:44,360 --> 00:39:45,030
Out!

886
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:48,330
Chen, watch him.

887
00:39:51,460 --> 00:39:52,390
What's going on?

888
00:39:52,590 --> 00:39:54,400
I... I confess.

889
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:55,840
I did it.

890
00:39:56,190 --> 00:39:57,720
Tell me how you did it first.

891
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:00,400
I pushed the cart over,

892
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:03,070
used a pole,
and hung the banner on the light.

893
00:40:03,670 --> 00:40:04,480
The street light is so high,

894
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:06,080
and you just hung it up there?

895
00:40:06,550 --> 00:40:07,510
Who are you kidding?

896
00:40:07,510 --> 00:40:08,840
If a young guy like me can't do it,

897
00:40:08,840 --> 00:40:10,900
how could my mentor, an old man, do it?

898
00:40:11,730 --> 00:40:13,190
Speak. What's the motive?

899
00:40:13,820 --> 00:40:14,380
Oh, man.

900
00:40:15,220 --> 00:40:16,340
Well,

901
00:40:16,800 --> 00:40:18,070
take my mentor—

902
00:40:19,120 --> 00:40:20,280
he's getting on in years,

903
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:22,070
selling grilled chicken ribs at a stall.

904
00:40:22,070 --> 00:40:24,760
The urban management officers
chase him around all day.

905
00:40:24,760 --> 00:40:26,000
Look what they did to my mentor.

906
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:27,030
I got angry.

907
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:28,840
I drank some alcohol,

908
00:40:28,840 --> 00:40:31,590
and I just hung it up.

909
00:40:31,710 --> 00:40:33,170
Was the alcohol you drank?

910
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:35,000
It was water that got in your head.

911
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:36,800
You've lost your mind, you know?

912
00:40:38,510 --> 00:40:39,400
Right. I... I...

913
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:40,670
Right, I also have...

914
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:44,000
Literally, I nearly drowned twice.

915
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:44,880
Give me a break.

916
00:40:45,440 --> 00:40:46,880
Once when I was little.

917
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:48,680
Mr. Ding fished me out back then.

918
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:49,510
Well...

919
00:40:52,190 --> 00:40:54,880
What am I saying?
Water got in when I was a kid.

920
00:40:55,030 --> 00:40:57,150
Then I fell into the sea

921
00:40:57,380 --> 00:40:59,630
in Japan last year.

922
00:40:59,630 --> 00:41:00,880
And in the sea,

923
00:41:01,280 --> 00:41:02,110
I almost drowned.

924
00:41:02,110 --> 00:41:03,510
I barely made it.

925
00:41:03,750 --> 00:41:04,670
Ever since I woke up,

926
00:41:04,670 --> 00:41:06,200
my brain hasn't been right.

927
00:41:06,360 --> 00:41:08,760
Complex PTSD.

928
00:41:08,760 --> 00:41:10,190
Needs hospitalization for observation.

929
00:41:10,190 --> 00:41:11,480
Right. The kid is sick.

930
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:12,610
Step aside. Shut up.

931
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:14,960
The hospital told you

932
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:16,110
to stay for observation.

933
00:41:16,110 --> 00:41:17,280
You didn't stay in the hospital,

934
00:41:17,280 --> 00:41:18,760
yet you came out.

935
00:41:19,420 --> 00:41:20,950
What are you doing out here?

936
00:41:21,150 --> 00:41:22,810
Will you pay for the hospital?

937
00:41:23,150 --> 00:41:24,560
Who can pay for my hospitalization?

938
00:41:24,560 --> 00:41:26,600
I have no money.
The plant won't reimburse me.

939
00:41:26,600 --> 00:41:27,690
Alright, alright.

940
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:29,320
Think clearly.

941
00:41:30,480 --> 00:41:33,620
Picking quarrels and provoking trouble
means at least 15 days' detention.

942
00:41:33,620 --> 00:41:35,220
Have you thought it through?

943
00:41:35,230 --> 00:41:37,280
But you can't wrongly accuse my mentor.

944
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:39,440
My mentor is old.

945
00:41:39,440 --> 00:41:41,630
Besides, he's a war hero.

946
00:41:41,630 --> 00:41:44,000
You can't arrest my mentor.

947
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:46,510
Fine.

948
00:41:47,470 --> 00:41:48,270
Take him away.

949
00:41:49,280 --> 00:41:49,800
Move.

950
00:41:51,360 --> 00:41:51,840
Xiao...

951
00:41:55,190 --> 00:41:56,110
Wait, Leng,

952
00:41:56,110 --> 00:41:58,770
you don't have to take him away.
What's this for?

953
00:41:58,960 --> 00:42:00,480
No need. It's no big deal. Why arrest him?

954
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:01,400
No big deal?

955
00:42:02,150 --> 00:42:03,150
Do you know

956
00:42:03,430 --> 00:42:06,580
the station square
is our city's image project?

957
00:42:06,950 --> 00:42:09,280
Picking quarrels and provoking trouble.

958
00:42:09,550 --> 00:42:11,880
Right? Fifteen days isn't too much, is it?

959
00:42:12,030 --> 00:42:13,460
No, how about this:

960
00:42:14,630 --> 00:42:15,440
investigating further.

961
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:16,550
What if you got the wrong person?

962
00:42:16,550 --> 00:42:17,590
This kid isn't right in the head.

963
00:42:17,590 --> 00:42:19,070
He's just talking nonsense here.

964
00:42:19,070 --> 00:42:20,280
He admitted it himself.

965
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,150
Ask him.

966
00:42:22,010 --> 00:42:23,940
It's okay. You hurry home.

967
00:42:23,970 --> 00:42:24,710
Don't worry.

968
00:42:24,740 --> 00:42:25,900
Are you stupid, kid?

969
00:42:26,600 --> 00:42:27,560
I'm fine.

970
00:42:28,310 --> 00:42:29,490
Keep your voice down.

971
00:42:29,490 --> 00:42:30,290
Get in the car.

972
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:32,150
Open the door yourself.

973
00:42:32,150 --> 00:42:33,510
Why are you getting in yourself?

974
00:42:33,510 --> 00:42:34,710
What are you doing?

975
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:35,840
What are you doing?

976
00:42:35,840 --> 00:42:36,480
Xiaoman!

977
00:42:36,480 --> 00:42:37,590
Go home now.

978
00:42:38,660 --> 00:42:39,750
I'm on duty.

979
00:42:39,960 --> 00:42:40,770
Step back.

980
00:42:48,230 --> 00:42:49,840
Xiaoman, that silly child!

981
00:42:58,320 --> 00:43:00,150
He actually took him away.

982
00:43:02,230 --> 00:43:03,800
Why couldn't I keep my hands to myself?

983
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:04,360
Why couldn't I?
